Description: Body sherd of Attic black-figured pottery skyphos; interior glazed black; exterior: black-figure decoration consisting of wing, rump and tail of sphinx to left (added red on wing; faded added white dots on band at start of long feathers and on alternating feathers; rump and tail in glaze fired reddish brown).
Bibliographic references: Venit 1982 / Painted Pottery from the Greek Mainland found in Egypt, 640-450 BC (p. 362, no. B476)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GA.0344) (Phase 1)
